benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/admin/queues - Get queues entries

covered: Valid Request: Many scenarios validate successful retrieval with various single and combined query parameters (TC01-TC10, TC23).
Empty Response: Covered (TC11, TC29) to verify behavior when no entries or filters exclude all data.

Query Parameters: Extensive coverage for valid and invalid params including accountId format and not-found (TC02, TC13, TC14), queueName (TC03), serviceName (TC04), minDate/maxDate (TC05, TC24, TC25), boolean flags (TC06-TC09, TC21, TC22).

Error Handling: Multiple error scenarios covered including invalid input (TC13, TC25), not found (TC14), internal server error (TC30), service unavailable and timeout (TC16, TC19), and injection/XSS attempts (TC17, TC26).
Non-functional / Resilience: Large-volume retrieval, performance expectation and concurrency covered (TC18, TC20), transient network recovery and retry (TC27).
Regression & Backward Compatibility: Regression test for withHistory and backward-compatibility for omitted params present (TC21, TC22).
Response correctness: Content-type validation and response status codes for success and error states are included (TC01, TC30, etc.).
gaps: Pagination: No scenarios exercise pagination (limit/offset/page size) or streaming/paged retrieval for very large result sets; important for GET with potentially large data.
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control, Last-Modified) or cache-related responses.
Rate Limiting / Throttling: No tests validate rate limits, throttling behavior, or proper 429 responses under high request rates.
Cache / Conditional Requests: No tests for conditional GET (If-None-Match / If-Modified-Since) behavior and 304 responses.

Content validation of octet-stream body: Tests assert content-type but do not validate the format/structure of the octet-stream payload (e.g., expected serialization, record boundaries, or parsing correctness).
Authorization scopes/roles: While unauthorized (no token) is covered, tests do not cover authorization granularity (e.g., insufficient permissions vs. admin role required), or 403 scenarios.
Pagination-related performance: Large-volume test (TC18) asserts response time but does not combine with pagination to verify page-time vs full-scan behavior.
recommendations: Add pagination tests: include limit/offset or page tokens, verify correct slicing of results, stable ordering, and behavior when requesting pages beyond available data.
Add caching tests: verify presence and correctness of Cache-Control, ETag, and Last-Modified headers; add conditional GET tests (If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since) expecting 304 where appropriate.
Add rate-limiting tests: simulate many requests to validate throttling behavior and correct 429 responses and Retry-After header handling.

Validate octet-stream payload: add tests that parse and validate the binary/octet-stream format returned to ensure expected record serialization and that filters affect the actual payload contents (not just metadata).
Add authorization role tests: verify responses for authenticated but unauthorized users (403) and ensure only admins can access this admin endpoint.
Combine pagination with large-data/performance tests: ensure acceptable response times for paged queries and that system degrades gracefully for very large datasets.
Add tests for conditional and malformed headers: e.g., invalid If-None-Match, unsupported Accept headers, and ensure the API responds with appropriate status codes and messages.
